summary: We are making smart computer friends that can help people make good choices in things like schools and hospitals to make the world a better place.
We are building awesome robots that can help people when they are hurt and help make the Earth cleaner and happier.
We are using very smart computers to solve tricky puzzles that can help doctors and scientists make new medicines and keep our planet healthy.
We are coming up with fun ways to make energy from the sun and wind so everyone can have lights and games without hurting nature.
We are learning how to make body parts like skin and bones with special printers so that everyone can feel better and play more.
We are teaching flying robots to deliver things like snacks and band-aids really fast without polluting the air.
We are building super fast zooming pods that can travel faster than racecars, taking people places without using much energy.
We are making special hats that let computers understand what you're thinking, so you can talk to them with your mind.
We are finding ways to fix owies in our bodies by telling the tiny parts inside us how to work better and keep us healthy.
We are asking big computers to help us look after Earth by telling us how to plant trees and clean the water.
We are building gardens that grow up instead of out, so everyone in the city can have fresh veggies without needing a lot of space.
We are sending robot helpers into the ocean to pick up trash and keep the fish and turtles happy and healthy.
We are creating magical materials that can bend, stretch, and heal themselves, and they are safe for the planet too.
We are making a computer school that helps every kid learn in their own special way, so school is fun for everyone.
We are sharing our toy-making secrets with everyone so that any kid, anywhere, can make their own amazing toys.
